'''Savannah Accelerated Development Authority''' (SADA) is a [[Government of Ghana]] agency responsible for coordinating a comprehensive development agenda for the [[savanna]] ecological zones comprising the three northernmost regions and stretches of [[Brong Ahafo Region|Brong Ahafo]] and [[Volta Region]]s that are contiguous to the Northern region of [[Ghana]]. Its mandate is to assist in the development of agriculture and industry in the region to help lessen the disparity between its development and that found elsewhere in the country.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://mofa.gov.gh/site/?page_id=282 | title=Savannah Accelerated Development Authority (SADA) | publisher=Ministry of Food & Agriculture, Republic of Ghana. | accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.modernghana.com/blogs/241637/31/the-savannah-accelerated-development-authority-sad.html | title=The Savannah Accelerated Development authority (sada) â€“is the north well positioned for it? | publisher=Modern Ghana | work=News Blog | date=1 October 2009 | accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/regional/artikel.php?ID=187244 | title=Savannah Accelerated Development Authority bill passed into law | publisher=Ghana Web | work=GNA | date=30 July 2010 | accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://northernghana.com/news/i/?n=1132 | title=Veep Holds Discussions On Savannah Accelerated Development Authority | publisher=Northernghana.com | date=2008 | accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref>

==Description==
Savannah Accelerated Development Authority was established by an Act of [[Parliament of Ghana|Parliament]]; SADA Act 805 on 17 September 2010 with its first Chief Executive Officer appointed in October 2011. It has a 5-year Business Plan which begun in 2012 and will end in 2016. Its office and staffing of directors and coordinators begun work in March 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sada-ghana.org/about-sada|title=SADA ACT & INSTITUTIONAL DEVELOPMENT|publisher=SADA Ghana|accessdate=24 November 2014}}</ref>

SADA will institute projects, programs and policies aimed at stimulating growth and addressing the human and social development needs of the target area. In the 2008 budget, the Government of Ghana mandated the preparation of a long term strategy to reverse decades of neglect of the northern part of Ghana and to set the pace for sustainable development.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sada-ghana.org/about-sada| title=Overview of SADA|publisher=SADA Ghana|accessdate=24 November 2014}}</ref>

